Lisa O. Monaco, Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, recently visited the United Kingdom to meet with senior British security and intelligence officials. The discussions focused on various bilateral security and counterterrorism issues, including efforts to combat ISIS, counter violent extremism, enhance intelligence cooperation, and prevent the flow of foreign fighters. Monaco emphasized the solidarity between the United States and the United Kingdom in fighting against violent extremism and discussed domestic and international programs aimed at countering violent extremism. The meeting also addressed ways to strengthen information sharing with European partners regarding potential threats to the United States and Europe.